project.name: Computer Management System
project.description:
I’m an active open-source developer and have created numerous projects.

The Computer Management System (CMS) is a comprehensive web-based solution designed for monitoring, managing, and controlling computers within an organization. It utilizes a centralized hub-and-spoke architecture, where the backend serves as the core orchestrator, facilitating real-time communication between the frontend user interface and the client-side agents. Key features include real-time status monitoring, remote command execution, and secure, automated agent updates.
